# Theme & Notification Patterns

## Theme Colors

All colors are centralized as `$script:` variables in `Initialize-Theme.ps1`. Categories:
- `MenuButton*` / `MenuButtonOnClick*` — menu bar normal + pressed states
- `MenuButtonShowIcon` / `MenuButtonSeparator` — icon prefix toggle and char
- `MenuButtonShowBrackets` / `MenuButtonBracket*` — bracket wrapping
- `DialogButton*` — dialog action button icon/bracket settings
- `Header*` / `Footer*` — chrome group backgrounds
- `HeaderRowBg` / `MenuRowBg` — per-row inset backgrounds
- `BorderPadV` / `BorderPadH` — blank-row/column border thickness
- `HeaderPauseButton` — pause/play emoji color in the header
- `HeaderSeparator` — full-width separator line color (used in `Write-MainFrame.ps1`)
- `*Dialog*` — per-dialog color sets (Quit, Settings, SettingsOffFocus, Time, Move, Info, Options, Theme)
- `StatsBox{Border,Title,Bg}` — outer stats panel chrome
- `Stats{Session,Movement,Performance,Travel,Settings}{Title,Label,Value}` — per-section granular colors
- `StatsInputs{Title,Label,Value}` — Detected Inputs sub-section colors
- `StatsCurve{Header,Line,Dots,Eq1,Eq2,Border}` — ease curve diagram colors
- `ThemeButton*` — dedicated colors for the `(t)heme` Settings dialog button

### Dialog Button Background and Hotkey Colors (Default Theme)

All dialog action button backgrounds use `"DarkCyan"` in the default theme (not `"Blue"`). All dialog button hotkey letters use `"Green"` in the default theme. Exception: in the debug theme, `MoveDialogButtonBg = "DarkGreen"` so `MoveDialogButtonHotkey` stays `"Yellow"` to remain visible. The debug theme `QuitDialogButtonHotkey` also uses `"White"` for distinctiveness on the `Magenta` background.

```powershell
# Default values (base + default theme):
$script:QuitDialogButtonBg     = "Magenta"
$script:QuitDialogButtonHotkey = "Green"
$script:TimeDialogButtonBg     = "DarkCyan"
$script:TimeDialogButtonHotkey = "Green"
$script:MoveDialogButtonBg     = "DarkCyan"
$script:MoveDialogButtonHotkey = "Green"
$script:InfoDialogButtonBg     = "DarkCyan"
$script:InfoDialogButtonHotkey = "Green"
$script:ThemeDialogButtonBg    = "DarkCyan"
$script:ThemeDialogButtonHotkey = "Green"
$script:SettingsDialogButtonBg     = "DarkCyan"
$script:SettingsDialogButtonHotkey = "Green"
```

When adding new theme colors:
1. Add `$script:NewColor = "..."` in the base variables section of `Initialize-Theme.ps1`
2. Add the same variable in **both** the `"default"` and `"debug"` `Apply` scriptblocks
3. Use via `Write-Buffer -FG $script:NewColor`
4. Update `AGENTS.md` color categories table

## Theme Profile System

`$script:ThemeProfiles` is an array of `@{ Name = "..."; Apply = { ... } }` hashtables. `Set-ThemeProfile -Name "..."` invokes the `Apply` scriptblock and updates `$script:CurrentThemeName` / `$script:CurrentThemeIndex`.

- `"default"` — transparent backgrounds everywhere except dialogs and on-click states
- `"debug"` — maximally distinct colors for all elements; `BorderPadV = 2`, `BorderPadH = 2`

Startup order: `default` → `debug` (if DebugMode) → `-Theme` param (overrides both). Debug toggle in `Show-OptionsDialog` auto-applies `"debug"` / `"default"` via `Set-ThemeProfile`.

## Emoji Handling

Emojis display as 2 columns but have string length 1. Compute positions statically:
```powershell
$emojiX = $startX
$pipeX = $emojiX + 2  # Emoji takes 2 display columns
Write-Buffer -X $emojiX -Y $row -Text $emoji -FG $color -BG $bg -Wide
Write-Buffer -X $pipeX -Y $row -Text "|" -FG $pipeColor -BG $bg
```

## Notification Fallback Chain

1. `$script:ToastAPI::ShowToast()` — native COM (instant)
2. `powershell.exe` subprocess — delegates to WinPS 5.1 WinRT support
3. `NotifyIcon.ShowBalloonTip()` — basic balloon (last resort)

Each toast uses a unique ephemeral AUMID (`svc_<PipeName>_<PID>_<seq>`). Registry key is created in `try`, toast fired, 50ms sleep, key removed in `finally`.

## Tray Icon

Background process only (`$script:_SkipTrayIcon = $true` in viewer). Uses `NotifyIcon` with `ContextMenuStrip` (Open, Pause/Resume, Quit). `DoEvents()` pumped every 50ms tick. `Update-TrayIcon` re-renders on title changes.

## Notification Bodies

Notification bodies must use `$script:WindowTitle` — never hardcoded internal terms ("Worker", "Viewer"):
```powershell
# CORRECT
Show-Notification -Body "$($script:WindowTitle) started (PID: $PID)" -Action started
Show-Notification -Body "$($script:WindowTitle) paused" -Action paused
Show-Notification -Body "$($script:WindowTitle) — terminal disconnected" -Action disconnected
```
